---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Use | One Less Thing"
  description="Terms of use for onelessthing.us. Free educational content, no financial advice, plain language."
>

  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <h1>Terms of use</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Plain language. No tricks. Here's what you're agreeing to by using this site.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container--narrow page-body">

    <p class="meta">Last updated: May 6, 2026 &middot; Questions? <a href="mailto:hayden@onelessthing.us">hayden@onelessthing.us</a></p>

    <section aria-labelledby="acceptance-heading">
      <h2 id="acceptance-heading">Using this site</h2>
      <p>
        By using onelessthing.us, you agree to these terms. If you don't agree, please
        don't use the site. We may update these terms over time — the "last updated"
        date above reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of the site means
        you accept any changes.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="content-heading">
      <h2 id="content-heading">What this site is</h2>
      <p>
        One Less Thing publishes free, plain-language educational content about disability
        financial planning — ABLE accounts, SSI (Supplemental Security Income), Medicaid,
        Special Needs Trusts, and related topics.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>This is educational content, not professional advice.</strong> Nothing on
        this site is legal advice, financial advice, or tax advice. Every situation is
        different, and the information here may not apply to yours. Always consult a
        qualified attorney, financial planner, or tax professional for decisions that
        affect your specific circumstances.
      </p>
      <p>
        Benefit rules — especially SSI, Medicaid, and ABLE account rules — change frequently
        and vary by state. We do our best to keep content current, but we cannot guarantee
        that every detail is up to date at the moment you read it. Verify important figures
        with official sources (Social Security Administration, your state's ABLE plan, etc.)
        before making decisions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="ip-heading">
      <h2 id="ip-heading">Content ownership</h2>
      <p>
        All content on this site — articles, guides, graphics, and other materials —
        is owned by One Less Thing Inc. unless otherwise noted. You may share links to
        our content freely. You may quote short excerpts with proper attribution.
        You may not reproduce full articles or republish our content without written
        permission.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you'd like to reprint or adapt something for a nonprofit, advocacy organization,
        or educational context, just ask — we're usually happy to work something out.
        Email <a href="mailto:hayden@onelessthing.us">hayden@onelessthing.us</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="conduct-heading">
      <h2 id="conduct-heading">How to use this site</h2>
      <p>This site is for personal, non-commercial use. You may not:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Scrape, crawl, or copy our content at scale for AI training or data resale.</li>
        <li>Use this site in a way that could damage, disable, or overburden our servers.</li>
        <li>Attempt to access any part of the site you're not authorized to access.</li>
        <li>Use our content in a way that misrepresents us or our positions.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="links-heading">
      <h2 id="links-heading">Links to other sites</h2>
      <p>
        We link to external sites — government agencies, nonprofit resources, other
        educational content — when they're useful. We don't control those sites and
        aren't responsible for their content or privacy practices. A link from us is
        not an endorsement.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="liability-heading">
      <h2 id="liability-heading">Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        One Less Thing Inc. provides this site and its content "as is." We make no
        warranties — express or implied — about the accuracy, completeness, or fitness
        for a particular purpose of any content here. To the fullest extent permitted
        by law, we are not liable for any damages arising from your use of this site
        or reliance on its content.
      </p>
      <p>
        This doesn't mean we're cavalier about accuracy — we care deeply about getting
        things right. It means we're a small company and cannot be responsible for
        decisions made based on educational content.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="governing-heading">
      <h2 id="governing-heading">Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Nebraska, without regard
        to conflict of law principles. Any disputes will be resolved in Nebraska courts.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="contact-heading">
      <h2 id="contact-heading">Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions? <a href="mailto:hayden@onelessthing.us">hayden@onelessthing.us</a>.
        We're a small team and will respond personally.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="disclaimer" role="note">
      <p>
        <em>This content is for educational purposes only and does not constitute legal, tax,
        or financial advice. Consult a qualified professional for your specific situation.</em>
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 3rem 0 2.5rem;
  }
  .page-header h1 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .lead { font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-body); }
  .page-body { padding: 3rem 1.5rem; }
  .meta { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .page-body section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .page-body h2 { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .page-body ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .page-body li { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .page-body p { margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .disclaimer {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0;
  }
  .disclaimer p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-muted); }
</style>
